This programme was launched by Microsoft in partnership with the Central University of Technology in 2020 with a pilot group of students from the Free State Department of Education. Eduvos signed the contract with them at the end of 2020 and we are delighted to announce that we will have our first intake in February 2022. Programme overview: The Microsoft Azure Artificial Intelligence Associate and Expert programme provides a comprehensive study in AI. This programme is aimed at a postgraduate level with some knowledge of programming, networking and math needed to gain entry. Azure AI Engineers use Cognitive Services, Machine Learning, and Knowledge Mining to architect and implement Microsoft AI solutions involving natural language processing, speech, computer vision, bots, and agents. The programme was built in collaboration with leading universities and employers to develop the skills employersâ€™ value by teaching them to explore, transform, model, and visualise data, and to create the next generation of intelligent solutions. Modules include:  Network+  Basic C# Programming  MS Certified: Azure Fundamentals  MS Certified: Azure AI Engineer Associate  MS Certified: Azure Developer Associate Each module will be followed by an examination. All Microsoft exams are stand-alone certifications that when combined form this programme. Once all certifications are completed, you will be a certified Microsoft AI Engineer. Certifications to complete:  CompTIA Network+  Basic C# Programming: Project, Theory and Practical exams  Microsoft Certified: Azure Fundamentals  Microsoft Certified: Azure AI Engineer Associate  Microsoft Certified: Azure Developer Associate Start today! Microsoft Azure Artificial Intelligence Engineeris offered fully online and virtual consultation will be made available to all students. It is also offered at the following campuses: Eduvos Pretoria and Eduvos Tyger Valley. Learn more about this world-leading qualification here.